author: The Associated Press
title: Florida State-Georgia Tech Preview Capsule
text:
Florida State-Georgia Tech Preview Capsule By The Associated Press -   
No. 9 Florida State (6-0, 4-0 ACC) at Georgia Tech (2-5, 0-4), 7 p.m. (ESPN2) 
Line: Florida State by 6 1-2. 
Series Record: Florida State leads 14-11-1. 
WHAT’S AT STAKE 
Florida State can’t afford to stumble if it wants to stay in the mix for the College Football Playoff, especially with a Nov. 7 trip to unbeaten Clemson looming. Georgia Tech, a preseason ACC favorite, has been a huge disappointment. The Yellow Jackets likely need an upset of the Seminoles to have a shot at maintaining their streak of 18 straight bowl appearances, tied for the second-longest active run in the country. 
KEY MATCHUP 
Florida State RB Dalvin Cook vs. Georgia Tech’s defensive front. Cook, a sophomore, ranks fifth in the nation with 955 yards rushing. He is averaging 8.7 yards per carry, has scored 10 touchdowns and seems set to have another big day. The Yellow Jackets have struggled to stop the running game, surrendering 178.4 yards per game to rank 84th nationally and next-to-last in the ACC. 
PLAYERS TO WATCH 
Florida State: QB Everett Golson. The transfer from Notre Dame has completed 67.2 percent of his passes for 1,449 yards and 11 touchdowns. He has yet to throw an interception. 
Georgia Tech: RB Marcus Marshall. The freshman rushed for 159 yards and two touchdowns in his first career start at B-back last week. 
FACTS & FIGURES 
Florida State is attempting to win its 29th consecutive ACC game, which would tie its own conference record. The Seminoles set the mark from 1992-95 during their first 29 conference games after joining the ACC. … Florida State’s last ACC loss was a 17-16 setback at North Carolina State on Oct. 6, 2012. … Under coach Paul Johnson, Georgia Tech is 2-1 against Top 10 opponents and 5-3 against ranked teams when playing at Bobby Dodd Stadium. … The Seminoles’ offense has yet to commit a turnover. … This will be the third opponent ranked in the Top 10 when facing Georgia Tech. The Yellow Jackets lost 30-22 at then-No. 8 Notre Dame and 43-24 at No. 6 Clemson. … Georgia Tech is finishing a stretch of six games against teams that have a combined record of 33-4 this season.
